President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Deborah J. Jeffrey as Inspector General for the Corporation for National and Community Service, and Mark J. Mazur as Assistant Secretary for Tax Policy in the Department of Treasury. He has also announced his intent to appoint Janie Barrera and Sherry Salway Black as members of the President's Advisory Council on Financial Capability. Deborah J. Jeffrey is a partner at Zuckerman Spaeder LLP and has extensive experience in civil and criminal investigations. Mark J. Mazur is currently the Deputy Assistant Secretary for Tax Analysis at the Department of Treasury. Janie Barrera is the founding president and CEO of ACCION Texas Inc., a nonprofit organization that provides small loans and management training. Sherry Salway Black is the Director of the Partnership for Tribal Governance at the National Congress of American Indians and has worked to improve the economic condition of Native Americans through promoting business development and financial literacy.